HEADWORD: Sheepbiter
<hw>Sheep"bit`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who practices
petty thefts.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There are political <qex>sheepbiters</qex> as well as pastoral;
betrayers of public trusts as well as of private.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

